vulnerabilities.title: Elevation Of Privileges
vulnerabilities.overview: send before 0.8.4 for Node.js uses a partial comparison for verifying whether a directory is within the document root, which allows remote attackers to access restricted directories, as demonstrated using 'public-restricted' under a 'public' directory.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS) Memory Consumption
vulnerabilities.overview: The qs module before 1.0.0 in Node.js does not call the compact function for array data, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) by using a large index value to create a sparse array.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: The qs module before 1.0.0 is vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) through a blocking event loop. The module does not check for object depth when parsing a string, therefore a deeply nested object will block the event loop.

vulnerabilities.title: Open Redirect
vulnerabilities.overview: The serve-static plugin before 1.7.2 is vulnerable to open redirects when mounted at root. Using a // (slash slash) followed by a domain in the PATH_INFO to the default URI, remote attackers are able to redirect users to other websites.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS) Using Non-standard Encodings
vulnerabilities.overview: express before 3.11.0 and  4.x before 4.5.0 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS).  express doesn't specify a charset field in the content-type header value when displaying 400 response messages. By not specifying a charset, an attacker can use non-standard encodings, such as UTF-7, to perform cross-site scripting attacks.

vulnerabilities.title: Information Disclosure
vulnerabilities.overview: Send versions before 0.11.1 may disclose files outside of the root webserver path.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: ms is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) attacks. The library takes a long time to parse a long string, allowing a malicious user to potentially crash the application by submitting an extremely large string.

vulnerabilities.title: Mishandled CORS Request Headers
vulnerabilities.overview: Hapi versions before 11.0.0 contain a flaw in the cross-origin resource sharing routing (CORS) procedure. If a connection which has CORS enabled for most routes and has one non-GET route with CORS disabled, the OPTIONS prefetch request will return the default CORS headers and the actual request will be returned with no CORS headers, effectively disabling CORS.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS) Socket Exhaustion
vulnerabilities.overview: hapi before 11.1.3  is vulnerable to denial of service (DoS) through Socket Exhaustion. If an incorrect Date is passed through the If-Modified-Since or Last-Modified headers, it may cause an 'Illegal Access' error to be thrown rather than sending a HTTP 500 back, hapi holds the socket open until the timeout is reached.

vulnerabilities.title: Connection Level Defaults Overwritten By CORS Config
vulnerabilities.overview: hapi before 11.1.4 applies the less restrictive security configuration when combining server level, connection level or route level CORS configurations.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: The moment JavaScript package has a flaw that passes untrusted user input to moment.duration(). Using the flaw, attackers can cause a Regular expression Denial of Service (ReDos) by blocking the event loop for a very long time.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: jQuery is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. All `text/javascript` responses and cross domain requests with non-explicit data types are executed, which allows a remote attacker to inject arbitrary Javascript into a victim's browser and perform unwanted actions on behalf of the user.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS) Through Assignment Of Constructor Properties
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is susceptible to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. It is vulnerable because it does not filter the assignment of constructor properties with unsafe strings.

vulnerabilities.title: UI Redress Attack Through Improper Sanitization Of SVG Elements
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is susceptible to UI redress attacks. The vulnerability is due to the lack of proper sanitisation of an html input string by stripping all potentially dangerous tokens. So, an attacker can place svg elements outside of the containing element, leading to rendering it over other elements on the page (example: a login link).

vulnerabilities.title: SQL Injection Through Arguments
vulnerabilities.overview: sequelize is vulnerable​ to SQL injection attacks. It is due to not properly handling the arguments' limit and order.

vulnerabilities.title: Timing Attack Vulnerability While Decoding
vulnerabilities.overview: cookie-signature is vulnerable to timing attacks. This vulnerability exists due to the way that a message is decoded. When comparing the value + secret against the value given, there is a direct comparison. This allows malicious users to work out the value of the secret based on how quickly a response is received from the decode function.

vulnerabilities.title: Authentication Bypass Through Wrong Configuration In Socket.io
vulnerabilities.overview: console-io has a flaw which leads to authentication bypass. It happens due to a misconfiguration which allows attackers to make a websocket connection without being authenticated. Using this websocket connection, attackers can send commands that will be executed as the user who is running the application.

vulnerabilities.title: Header Injection Via Byte Truncation
vulnerabilities.overview: hapi is vulnerable to header injection attacks. The vulnerablilty exists because response headers are improperly formed by truncating high bit, allowing attackers to perform header injection.

details.fixText: To mitigate the issue, please apply the fix patch from link below.

vulnerabilities.title: SQL Injection Circumventing Database Access Controls
vulnerabilities.overview: sequelize is vulnerable to indirect SQL injection attacks. Due to a lack of proper user input validation, it is possible to avoid the database access controls to gain restricted information.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS) Through Media Plugin
vulnerabilities.overview: TinyMCE is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. This vulnerability is caused by the media plugin not correctly filtering out script attributes.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS) Via Validation Response
vulnerabilities.overview: hapi is susceptible to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. The attack is possible because validation responses are not properly escaped.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS) Through Error Messages
vulnerabilities.overview: boom is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. The vulnerability exists because error response messages are not properly validated.

vulnerabilities.title: Internal Route Access Bypass
vulnerabilities.overview: hapi does not correct restrict internal route usage. It does not check the 'allowInternals' option when a server.inject() call is made to an internal route.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: negotiator is vulnerable to to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) attacks. A malicious user can use the "Accept-Language" header to cause a ReDoS via a string value.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS) Through Large Websocket Message
vulnerabilities.overview: ws is vulnerable to denial of service (DoS) attacks. The vulnerability exists as there was no default max value for a websocket payload size. A malicious user can send an excessively large websocket message to cause a DoS on the server.

vulnerabilities.title: Validation Bypass Via Invalid Input
vulnerabilities.overview: The call package is vulnerable to validation bypass attacks. A malicious user can bypass the route validation rules by passing a set of empty parameters to the call library.

vulnerabilities.title: Remote Memory Disclosure
vulnerabilities.overview: Sequelize allows malicious users to obtain unauthorized information such as TLS keys or database passwords. When a number is passed as a parameter to the buffer function, nodejs will return a block of memory. This memory may contain passwords or other sensitive information.

vulnerabilities.title: Arbitrary Code Execution Via Constructor Access
vulnerabilities.overview:
The angularjs library is vulnerable to arbitrary code execution by allowing access to the constructors. A malicious user can access constructors by passing arbitrary code to the ensureSafeAssignContext function in $parse.

Note: The angularjs expression sandboxing is not meant to be used for security reasons. Developers are encouraged to disallow users to modify the client-side templates.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is susceptible to cross-site scripting attacks.This vulnerability happens because angular does not sanitize `xlink:href` attributes.

vulnerabilities.title: Timing Attack Via Signature Validation
vulnerabilities.overview: cookie-signature is vulnerable to timing attacks. The vulnerability can be caused due to the use of `exports.sign` method to validate and retrieve the signed value.

vulnerabilities.title: Insecure Pseudorandom Number Generation
vulnerabilities.overview: ws is vulnerable to insecure pseudorandom number generation. The vulnerability exists because it uses Math.random() which does not provide cryptographically secure random numbers.

vulnerabilities.title: SQL Injection
vulnerabilities.overview: sequelize is vulnerable to SQL injection. It improperly escapes bound arrays of strings on Postgres, SQLite, and Microsoft SQL Server, making it vulnerable to SQL injection.

vulnerabilities.title: Content-Security-Policy Bypass
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is vulnerable to Content-Security-Policy bypasses in firefox and chrome browsers. A malicious user can bypass the content-security-policy if the browser has an extension installed that uses angular by auto-boostrapping angular.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. A malicious user can inject and execute arbitrary javascript because the sanitizer has not blacklisted the usemap attribute which could only reference unsanitized content.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: hoek is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. It does not comprehensively escape html and javascript.

vulnerabilities.title: Timing Attacks
vulnerabilities.overview: cookie-signature is vulnerable to timing attacks. The library is vulnerable because they do not compare MACs in constant-time, which allows malicious users to use the timing of the request to progressively identify a valid MAC hashes.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Via Sandbox Escaping
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is vulnerable to cross-site scripting attacks. A malicious user can inject arbitrary javascript by executing angular expressions with sandbox escape characters in them. Starting from version 1.6 onwards, the sandbox feature has been removed from angular. To mitigate this issue, developers should avoid dynamically generating angular templates, or expressions, if a user input can reach the expression.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Override Protection Bypass
vulnerabilities.overview: qs is vulnerable to prototype override protection bypass. It is possible for an attacker to bypass the protection and overwrite prototype properties and functions by prefixing the name of the parameter with `[ `or `]`. Overwriting these properties on the object prototype can impact application logic, potentially allowing attackers to change security controls, modify data, and cause even worse impact.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: content is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS) attacks. Attackers can use malicious content-type or content-disposition headers to trigger the attack since it does not properly handle the OWS parametes in the headers.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: debug is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS). The regular expression is used to map `%o` to `util.inspect()` can take awhile for long strings, hanging an application.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: parsejson is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS) attacks. An attacker can pass a `JSON` file to the library that when parsed can cause a ReDoS.

details.fixText: Use JSON.parse() instead of this library.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: mime is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS) attacks. The library does not restrict the type of characters that it takes in, causing the application to take a long time to process. A malicious user can use this behaviour to cause a ReDoS.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: fresh is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS).The vulnerability exists when matching multiple ETags in `If-None-Match` which causes the event loop to be blocked.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: moment is vulnerable to denial of service (DoS) attacks. These attacks are possible because the regular expression that is used for matching dates takes awhile for long strings.

vulnerabilities.title: Mutation Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is vulnerable to mutation cross-site scripting (XSS) attack. A malicious user can inject arbitrary Javascript through the `innerHTML` property that is then executed when the browser mutates it.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: ws is vulnerable to denial of service (DoS) attacks. A malicious user can pass a `GET` request to the application with a `Sec-WebSocket-Extensions` header that uses the `Object.prototype` property name to crash the application.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: lodash is vulnerable to prototype pollution attacks. Attackers can add or modify existing properties relating to an Object by using the utilities function to change the prototype of said Object. Using this flaw, attackers can trigger denial of service (DoS) attacks and in some situations remote code execution(RCE) attacks.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: hoek is vulnerable to prototype pollution attacks. Attackers can add or modify existing properties relating to an Object by using the utilities function to change the prototype of said Object. Using this flaw, attackers can trigger denial of service (DoS) attacks and in some situations remote code execution (RCE) attacks.

vulnerabilities.title: Regular Expression Denial Of Service (ReDoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: validator is vulnerable to regular expression denial of service (ReDoS) attacks. A malicious user can pass a base64 string that when validated by the application will cause a ReDoS attack.

vulnerabilities.title: Directory Traversal
vulnerabilities.overview: ponse is vulnerable to directory traversal attacks. The library does not properly validate user input when fetching resources, allowing a malicious user to gain access to sensitive information by sending a http request.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution Attack
vulnerabilities.overview: lodash is vulnerable to prototype pollution attack. The vulnerability exists due to the ability to inject properties on Object.prototype, which allows DoS, and possibly other forms of attacks.

vulnerabilities.title: SQL Injection
vulnerabilities.overview: sequelize is vulnerable to SQL injection when using with PostgreSQL. This is due to backslashes that are not being escaped properly in non-standard strings, allowing a remote attacker to inject and execute arbitrary SQL statements in the database.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: jquery is vulnerable to prototype pollution attacks. The vulnerability exists as it is possible to overwrite `Object.prototype` with arbitrary object properties.

vulnerabilities.title: SQL Injection
vulnerabilities.overview: sequelize is vulnerable to sql injection attacks. The attacks are possible because the library does not escape the JSON path key provided by the user using postgres dialects in `query-generator.js`.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: lodash is vulnerable to prototype pollution. The vulnerability exists due to the ability to inject properties in `_.defaultsDeep`, which allows DoS, and possibly other forms of attacks.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: subtext is vulnerable to denial of service. The `maxBytes` configuration is not enforced for payloads with chunked encoding that are written to the file system. This allows attackers to send requests with arbitrary payload sizes, which may exhaust system resources leading to an application crash.

vulnerabilities.title: Memory Leaks
vulnerabilities.overview: socket.io-adapter is vulnerable to memory leak.This occurs because the function `Adapter.prototype.del` in `index.js` leaves a room without properly validating the closure of a socket, allowing an attacker to trigger memory leaks by sending the `leave` signals.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: tinymce is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). The attack exists because it does not prevent the attacker from injecting a malicious script into the editor via the clipboard or APIs, allowing to execute the script when a user loads the editor.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: @hapi/subtext is vulnerable to prototype pollution. Lack of object validation allows an attacker to inject arbitrary Object properties which can potentially lead to execution of arbitrary code.

details.fixText: This package is deprecated. Upgrade to @hapi/subtext 6.1.2.

vulnerabilities.title: Denial Of Service (DoS)
vulnerabilities.overview: @hapi/ammo is vulnerable to denial of service (DoS).  The Range HTTP header parser causes the function to throw a system error when the header value is invalid, allowing an attacker to crash the application using a malicious header value.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution
vulnerabilities.overview: minimist is vulnerable to prototype pollution. The library allows an attacker to modify properties of Object.prototype using a `constructor` or `__proto__` payload.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: jquery is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). The vulnerability exists as the htmlPrefilter method intercepted html code that can cause unwanted HTML to be rendered.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: jquery is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). When passing a HTML from untrusted sources to one of jQuery's DOM manipulation methods (i.e. .html(), .append(), and others), untrusted code may potentially be executed.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: jquery is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). When passing a HTML containing `<option>` elements to one of jQuery's DOM manipulation methods (i.e. .html(), .append(), and others), untrusted code may potentially be executed.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: angular is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). The vulnerability exists as the regex-based replacement, `XHTML_TAG_REGEXP`, could convert sanitized code which has `<option>` wrapped into `<select>`,  into unsanitized code.

vulnerabilities.title: Code Injection
vulnerabilities.overview: lodash is vulnerable to injection vulnerability. An attacker can inject malicious code via `sourceURL` since it is not sanitized for the user-provided code that leads to the `eval()` function.

vulnerabilities.title: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
vulnerabilities.overview: tinymce is vulnerable to cross-site scripting (XSS). An attacker is able to inject and execute arbitrary Javascript in a user's browser when the library is configured in classic editing mode. The stripping and sanitization logic of TinyMCE can be bypassed using nested and non-terminated HTML tags, which can allow an attacker to inject an `` tag with arbitrary `src` and `onerror` values.
